    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson**, whose 83.29 efficiency score makes him the clear must-start. Facing McCullers Jr. (4.94 xERA), **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park factor boost and an ideal platoon alignment, while his propensity for swiping bags is further buoyed by a slow delivery from the opposing starter. Similarly, **Jacob Wilson** presents a high-floor, high-ceiling profile (74.08); hitting atop the order against Cameron provides the volume necessary to hunt stolen bases, a priority given our league's scarcity weighting. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (71.02) faces a respectable arm in Ober, his elite xwOBA metrics and top-of-the-order positioning cement him as a core play despite the slight platoon disadvantage.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical tightropes elsewhere. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (60.56) remains a strong play specifically due to his platoon edge, though he faces a stiff test against Peralta. Conversely, **Nasim Nunez** (47.72) is a marginal start, but we keep him active primarily for his speed utility; the presence of an elite catcher behind the plate is a negative factor for his stolen base probability, but the opposing pitcher's slow delivery speed effectively offsets that risk. **Coby Mayo** (43.81) barely cleared our threshold, as his favorable park environment helps mask the downside of hitting in the eight-hole against Lambert. **Drake Baldwin** (54.14) and **Heliot Ramos** (54.96) serve as steady, albeit unspectacular, pivots to round out the batting order.\n\nOur bench decision-making today was relatively straightforward due to league-wide scheduling gaps. With **Kyle Tucker**, **Andy Pages**, and **Jackson Merrill** all inactive, we are effectively playing with a shortened roster, while **Luis Robert Jr.** remains sidelined on the IL. Consequently, players like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Lowe**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Miguel Vargas**, **Brady House**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Liam Hicks** are unavailable to provide depth today. The primary risk remains the volatility of the back-end starters; should weather reports shift or late lineup changes shuffle the batting order for **Drake Baldwin** or **Coby Mayo**, we may see their efficiency scores dip below our floor, necessitating a careful watch on pre-game confirmations.",
